Original Fortran code that was used for the parent C port

  This directory contains the
  limited memory code for solving
  large unconstrained optimization
  problems.

   sdrive.f -  is a simple driver
   lbfgs.f  -  contains all the supporting
               routines
   makefile -  a makefile for Unix users

Per http://users.iems.northwestern.edu/~nocedal/lbfgs.html

Condition for Use: This software is freely available for educational or commercial purposes. We expect that all publications describing work using this software quote at least one of the references given below. This software is released under the BSD License

Authors
Jorge Nocedal
References
J. Nocedal. Updating Quasi-Newton Matrices with Limited Storage (1980), Mathematics of Computation 35, pp. 773-782.
D.C. Liu and J. Nocedal. On the Limited Memory Method for Large Scale Optimization (1989), Mathematical Programming B, 45, 3, pp. 503-528.

